                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Garrett</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Hague, Netherlands</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-11-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 2, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 800.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to Mr. Newel’s No. 790, of October 3,
                    in connection with the meeting of the arbitral tribunal in the Japanese
                    house-tax case, I have the honor to state that the secretary-general of the
                    Permanent Court of Arbitration informs me that the first meeting of the tribunal
                    will take place at The Hague on the 21st instant; and, further, that the
                    Governments of France, Germany, and Great Britain have collectively designated
                    the following gentlemen as their agents to form a joint delegation to appear
                    before the tribunal, viz: <list>
                        <item>The Government of France: Mr. Fromageot, LL. D., advocate at the court
                            of appeal at Paris.</item>
                        <item>The Government of Germany: Mr. Weipert, unattached consul.</item>
                        <item>The Government of Great Britain: Mr. Ambrose B. Walford.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John W. Garrett.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
